<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Small dark species with strong prealar, 2+3 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">dc</emphasis>
and strong costal spine. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wulp" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Drymeia aterrima" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aterrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Drymeia aterrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Wulp, 1896), especially in the dark male calypter, but can be distinguished from it in the male by a broad frontal vitta (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Drymeia ponti sp. nov. A male habitus, paratype B male head, frontal view C male mid femur, anterodorsal view D male hind tibia, anterior view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.60393.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520354" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">13B</figureCitation>
) and a distinct ventral apical process on 
<collectionCode name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics">T</collectionCode>
3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Drymeia ponti sp. nov. A male habitus, paratype B male head, frontal view C male mid femur, anterodorsal view D male hind tibia, anterior view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.60393.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520354" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">13D</figureCitation>
), and in the female by the presence of a flattened fore tarsomere 5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Drymeia ponti sp. nov. A female habitus, paratype B female head, frontal view C female tarsomeres 3 - 5. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B); 0.5 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.60393.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520356" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">15C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
